  "doc_id": "6601",
  "text": "Furthermore, we show that our method is robust with respect to randomly assigned genes in the gene groups. Therefore the biological profiles do not depend critically on the details of the prior analysis yielding the groups, e.g. threshold, parameters of cluster analysis methods, and normalizations. For the cell-cycle data of Ref. [CITATION_1] we demonstrate that the profiles allow a reasonable biological interpretation of the gene groups. No clearly irrelevant terms are reported. The fact that we can separate mitosis and replication confirms the initial grouping by Whitfield et al. [CITATION_2] Therefore, we conclude that our framework is indeed sensitive enough to find the relevant biological profiles in gene groups.",
